docs.lead_paragraph: One of the most significant recent trends in European publishing is the growing interest in translations from the Serbo-Croatian. The names of the Bosnian Ivo Andric, author of historical chronicles and winner of a 1961 Nobel Prize, and the Montenegrin Miodrag Bulatovic, who wrote "Hero on a Donkey," are already well known. Attention is now shifting to avant garde writers hitherto ignored abroad and to the monumental works of the elderly Miroslav Krleza.
